cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper presents an active learning architecture for a robot to acquire motor skills and generalise over its experience. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses learning strategies and goals for the robot. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is relevant as the paper presents an intelligent system that can actively learn and make decisions. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is possible as the robot may use vision to explore its environment and learn from its teachers. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also possible as the paper discusses the framework of life-long strategic learning, which involves control and decision-making.
